title: Further Foolishness
creator: Stephen Leacock
description: LibriVox recording of Further Foolishness, by Stephen Leacock. Read by TriciaG. Seventeen goofy stories and essays by Canadian humourist Stephen Leacock. "Professor Leacock has made more people laugh with the written word than any other living author. One may say he is one of the greatest jesters, the greatest humorist of the age." – A. P. Herbert (Introduction by TriciaG & Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (155MB)
subject: audiobook; librivox; humor; canadian humour
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: The stories were hard to follow and get into.  I listened to the first four chapters 2x and it was just too boring for me.  Gave up and moved on.
reviews.reviewtitle: I did not like this book
